newsitem.title: CHINA: Shanghai soybean ends mixed on uncertainty.
newsitem.headline: Shanghai soybean ends mixed on uncertainty.

text.p: Shanghai soybean futures ended mixed on Tuesday, with the short-term market trend unclear, traders said.
The key January 1997 contract ended at 3,171 yuan ($382) per tonne, unchanged from Monday's close. It opened at 3,171 and stayed at that level for the whole session.
March rose 19 to 3,219 yuan per tonne, May 25 to 3,285, July was unchanged at 3,360, September fell 20 to 3,360 and the first traded November 1997 contract ended at 3,420.
Combined volume rose to 13,300 tonnes from 11,300.
Traders said many investors stayed on the sidelines due to uncertainty over the short-term market trend.
"Soybean continued to consolidate today in an absence of market-moving news, making investors unwilling to hold positions," one trader said.
Analysts expect soybean to consolidate in a narrow range in the next few days.
